Common Ports and Their Software Implementations
Web Servers and Proxies

Port 80 (HTTP)

Apache HTTP Server

Default config: /etc/apache2/apache2.conf
Common modules: mod_ssl, mod_rewrite, mod_proxy


Nginx

Default config: /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
Known for: reverse proxy, load balancing


IIS (Internet Information Services)

Windows-based
Management via IIS Manager


Caddy

Modern auto-HTTPS server
Simple Caddyfile configuration




Port 443 (HTTPS)

Same software as Port 80, with SSL/TLS configuration
Let's Encrypt - Common SSL provider
Certbot - Automated certificate management



Database Servers

Port 3306

MySQL

Default config: /etc/mysql/my.cnf
Management: MySQL Workbench, phpMyAdmin


MariaDB

Fork of MySQL
Compatible with MySQL tools




Port 5432

PostgreSQL

Default config: postgresql.conf
Tools: pgAdmin, psql, DBeaver


Amazon RDS PostgreSQL

Managed PostgreSQL service


EnterpriseDB

Enterprise PostgreSQL distribution




Port 1433

Microsoft SQL Server

Management Studio (SSMS)
SQL Server Express (free version)


Azure SQL Database

Cloud-based SQL Server





Email Servers

Port 25 (SMTP)

Postfix

Default on many Linux distributions
Config: /etc/postfix/main.cf


Microsoft Exchange Server

Windows-based enterprise solution


Exim

Default on Debian systems


SendMail

One of the oldest SMTP servers




Port 143 (IMAP) & 110 (POP3)

Dovecot

Modern IMAP/POP3 server
Often paired with Postfix


Courier Mail Server

Integrated mail solution


Microsoft Exchange

Enterprise-grade solution


Zimbra

Open-source collaboration suite





File Transfer

Port 21 (FTP)

vsftpd

"Very Secure FTP Daemon"
Common on Linux


FileZilla Server

Popular Windows FTP server


ProFTPD

Feature-rich FTP server


Pure-FTPd

Security-focused FTP server




Port 22 (SSH/SFTP)

OpenSSH

Default on most Unix systems
Includes SFTP server


Bitvise SSH Server

Windows SSH/SFTP server


WinSCP

Windows SFTP client


MobaXterm

Enhanced terminal with SFTP





Cache & Queue Servers

Port 6379

Redis

Default config: redis.conf
Tools: Redis Desktop Manager
Variants: Redis Stack, Redis Enterprise




Port 11211

Memcached

Simple memory caching
Tools: PHPMemcachedAdmin
Used by: Facebook, Wikipedia





Message Brokers

Port 5672 (AMQP)

RabbitMQ

Management interface on port 15672
Plugins for multiple protocols


Apache ActiveMQ

Java-based message broker
Supports multiple protocols





Development Servers

Port 3000

Node.js

Express.js
Next.js
React Development Server


Ruby on Rails

Development environment




Port 8080

Apache Tomcat

Java servlet container


Jenkins

CI/CD server


Spring Boot

Java applications


Jetty

Java web server





Container & Orchestration

Port 2375/2376

Docker

Daemon API ports
Docker Registry (port 5000)


Kubernetes

API Server (port 6443)
kubelet (port 10250)





Monitoring & Metrics

Port 9090

Prometheus

Metrics collection


Node Exporter (9100)

System metrics




Port 3000

Grafana

Visualization platform


Kibana

Elasticsearch frontend





Directory Services

Port 389 (LDAP)

OpenLDAP

Open source implementation


Active Directory

Microsoft's directory service


Apache Directory Server

Java-based LDAP server





Remote Access

Port 3389 (RDP)

Windows Remote Desktop Services

Built into Windows Server


xrdp

RDP server for Linux


FreeRDP

Open source RDP implementation




Port 5900 (VNC)

TightVNC

Cross-platform VNC


RealVNC

Commercial VNC solution


TigerVNC

High-performance VNC


UltraVNC

Windows-focused VNC
